LOCALIZATION FOR LINUX SYSTEMS
==============================

1. Generate po files from source code

	find .. -name "*.cpp" -o -name "*.h" | xargs xgettext --keyword=_ --language=C++ -o esteid-browser-plugin.pot
	find .. -name "*.ui" | xargs xgettext --language=Glade -j -o esteid-browser-plugin.pot

	If you are generating the file for the language *for the first time*:
		msginit -l et_EE --no-translator -o esteid-browser-plugin-et.po -i esteid-browser-plugin.pot

	If there *already is* a po file for your language:
		msgmerge --update esteid-browser-plugin-et.po esteid-browser-plugin.pot

2. Translate and fill/update the po file headers

	nano esteid-browser-plugin-et.po

3. Generate translation files for the system

	mkdir -p et_EE/LC_MESSAGES
	msgfmt -c -v -o et_EE/LC_MESSAGES/esteid-browser-plugin.mo esteid-browser-plugin-et.po

4. Test translations

	mkdir -p /usr/share/locale/et_EE/LC_MESSAGES/
	cp et_EE/LC_MESSAGES/esteid-browser-plugin.mo /usr/share/locale/et_EE/LC_MESSAGES/

